The one genuinely defensible issue is the `@spec` on the `init/1` **GenServer callback**: it narrows the argument domain to `keyword()`, while the `GenServer.init/1` callback contract is `term()`. A callback implementation must accept everything the behaviour may pass it, so a narrowed callback spec is the kind of thing the compiler's type checking flags. I also removed the `import Bitwise` in favor of fully-qualified calls to eliminate any import-related warning surface, and hardened the `:secret` validation into a pattern match (no stray `unless`-as-statement).

